HEADWORD: Potboiler
<hw>Pot"boil`er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A term applied
derisively to any literary or artistic work, and esp. a painting, done
simply for money and the means of living.</def> <mark>[Cant]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

